column5: This has been going on and expanding in usage since 2019 and before. The proposed bill only sets a new standard for the current expansion of the technology. Hard saying if the current expansion would meet or exceed the proposed requirements. Probably a "feel good" piece of legislation that will have no real effect to the trajectory of the expansion as is currently in the works.
They sure use the heck out of that drive thru scanner at the Ifalls crossing. Lol.
Scanning for illegal crawlers n salted minnow.
I wonder how many people are smuggled in under boat covers !

Crossed back over at midnight last night. Guy saw the rod tubes and says "oh fisherman" he asked where we come from I says Nakina. He asked how we did I said great trip lots of big pike and finally he asked if we were bringing anything back and I says no. Pretty basic if you ask me.
